                                                                                                                            Preamble

                      This software is created as a learning resource to help others understand how to use Allegro 5 to develop games in C or C++. While many developers rely on modern game engines, this project encourages a return to low-level game programming to help aspiring developers build a deeper understanding of how games work under the hood.

            The Ryan Public License allows you to freely study, modify, and build upon the source code for educational or creative purposes. However, it includes a few conditions to ensure that credit is preserved and that the original author’s work is not misrepresented.

                                                                                                          Terms and Conditions
  
